title: Too Rusty? 'Jet Rocket' panel..1300+pics..13,000+ miles now

posts.content:
Great to see you at Harewood the other week fella and really chuffed the jet rocket made a RULE line up before going to the the new owner....On wards and upward well downwards and inwards with the new project if what you got planned comes off ....im wondering whats under that silver cover

rememember your new resto project thread is more than welcome over on RULE


Sean

notasprint wrote:I always keep an eye out for Jet Rocket when I'm over at the refinery, look forward to spotting your new ride in the car park.

Jet Rocket certainly looked good as you passed us on the A1 close to the M62 on the way home from Harewood House last week.

Good luck with your new resto.

Thanks dude, it was my last run out and enjoyed every minute of it, exspecially the mad dash I made to a mates house after I taken the family home

moler wrote:Carried on with the holes today, and got to the point where I needed to do some of the detail bending, I made this former...






...bit of hammering later...


...did the same to the drag link hole...


...cut the other holes out that I'd left in for strength, then I did the long bends, this is when I discovered that I should have done these first, DOH! but I got there in the end...




...very pleased with this...






Great work!!!!
I have just started my journey, I am having the cross plate problem, but I have non to use as a template, you don't have the old panel or the dimensions jotted down somewhere do you by chance.
Cheers Dave
Sorry Dave I don't...this is a long shot, but Kieft and Klok had a pile of NOS ones at EBi a few years ago???
